    <main>
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="container">
                <h1>Sinners and Saints</h1>
                <p class="section-intro">Understanding archetypal patterns through the VC lens</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="container">
                <h2>The Opening Paradox</h2>
                
                <div class="opening-truth">
                    <p class="big-text">There are no sinners. There are no saints.</p>
                    <p class="big-text">There is only VC.</p>
                    
                    <div class="explanation">
                        <p>What we call "good" and "evil," "sinner" and "saint" are just different VC ranges operating through human nervous systems.</p>
                        <p><strong>High VC = Behaviors we label "good"</strong></p>
                        <p><strong>Low VC = Behaviors we label "evil"</strong></p>
                        <p>Not morality. Capacity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>The Archetypal Spectrum</h2>
                
                <div class="archetype-ranges">
                    <div class="archetype-box">
                        <h3>VC 0-15: The Collapsed</h3>
                        <p class="archetype-description"><strong>"The Sinner at Breaking Point"</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Cannot process basic reality</li>
                            <li>Desperate for relief (any method)</li>
                            <li>Destructive to self and others</li>
                            <li>No capacity for complexity</li>
                            <li>System in emergency mode</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="archetype-truth">Not evil. Collapsed. Needs emergency support.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="archetype-box">
                        <h3>VC 15-31: The Suppressed Majority</h3>
                        <p class="archetype-description"><strong>"The Everyday Sinner"</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Chronic dysfunction masked as normal</li>
                            <li>Causes harm without awareness</li>
                            <li>Needs external regulation</li>
                            <li>Projects shadow constantly</li>
                            <li>This is most of humanity</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="archetype-truth">Not bad people. Low capacity operating at species average.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="archetype-box">
                        <h3>VC 31-60: The Integrating</h3>
                        <p class="archetype-description"><strong>"The Reforming Sinner / Aspiring Saint"</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Cement breaking, awareness increasing</li>
                            <li>Can see own shadow</li>
                            <li>Taking responsibility</li>
                            <li>Doing the work</li>
                            <li>Functionality improving</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="archetype-truth">The hero's journey. Most spiritual/therapeutic work happens here.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="archetype-box">
                        <h3>VC 60-102: The Integrated</h3>
                        <p class="archetype-description"><strong>"The Saint"</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Operating near human baseline</li>
                            <li>Can hold paradox</li>
                            <li>Process complexity</li>
                            <li>Respond vs react</li>
                            <li>Help others rise</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="archetype-truth">Not morally superior. Just higher capacity for this substrate interface.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="archetype-box">
                        <h3>VC 102+: The Expanded</h3>
                        <p class="archetype-description"><strong>"The Mystic / Sage"</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Temporary access to higher states</li>
                            <li>Direct substrate perception</li>
                            <li>Wisdom downloads</li>
                            <li>Returns to baseline with insights</li>
                            <li>Teaches what they've seen</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="archetype-truth">Peak experiences. Can't live here. Visit, learn, return, integrate.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Classic Archetypes Reinterpreted</h2>
                
                <div class="classic-archetypes">
                    <div class="classic-archetype">
                        <h3>The Addict (VC 10-25)</h3>
                        <p>Not weak. Not moral failure. <strong>Seeking external regulation because internal regulation is broken.</strong></p>
                        <p>Treatment: Raise VC → Internal regulation returns → External regulation no longer needed</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="classic-archetype">
                        <h3>The Narcissist (VC 15-30)</h3>
                        <p>Not evil. <strong>Cement so thick they can't feel others.</strong> What looks like selfishness = literally cannot access empathy at current capacity.</p>
                        <p>Path: Break cement → Feel others → Behavior changes naturally</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="classic-archetype">
                        <h3>The Abuser (VC 5-20)</h3>
                        <p>Not monster. <strong>Unprocessed pain projected outward.</strong> Hurt people hurt people = Low VC people lower others' VC.</p>
                        <p>Solution: Raise their VC (difficult, may not be possible) OR protect others from low-VC harm</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="classic-archetype">
                        <h3>The Martyr (VC 25-40)</h3>
                        <p>Not noble. <strong>Can't set boundaries (too low VC to hold complexity of "I matter AND you matter").</strong></p>
                        <p>Growth: Raise VC → Can hold both truths → Set healthy boundaries</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="classic-archetype">
                        <h3>The Sage (VC 80-102)</h3>
                        <p>Not enlightened being. <strong>Human at baseline capacity.</strong> What looks like wisdom = Normal human functioning when cement is broken.</p>
                        <p>Truth: We're ALL supposed to be here. VC = 102 was average for 190,000 years.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>The Compassion This Creates</h2>
                
                <div class="compassion-section">
                    <h3>If There's No Good/Evil, Just VC...</h3>
                    
                    <div class="compassion-implications">
                        <p><strong>Then:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>That "asshole" = Low VC, not bad person</li>
                            <li>That "saint" = High VC, not morally superior</li>
                            <li>Your failures = Low VC moments, not character flaws</li>
                            <li>Their harm = Capacity issue, not evil nature</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p><strong>Which means:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Compassion becomes easier (they're capacity-limited)</li>
                            <li>Boundaries become clearer (protect from low-VC harm)</li>
                            <li>Judgment becomes pointless (judging capacity, not morality)</li>
                            <li>Hope becomes real (VC is changeable)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="compassion-limits">
                        <h3>BUT: Compassion ≠ Tolerance of Harm</h3>
                        <p>Understanding someone operates at VC = 10 doesn't mean accepting their harmful behavior.</p>
                        <p><strong>You can have compassion AND boundaries.</strong></p>
                        <p>"I understand you're at low VC. AND I'm protecting myself/others from low-VC harm."</p>
                        <p>Both true. That's the paradox high VC can hold.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Your Archetype Changes With Your VC</h2>
                
                <div class="archetype-fluidity">
                    <p class="big-text">You're not ONE archetype. You're a VC range.</p>
                    
                    <div class="personal-ranges">
                        <p><strong>Monday VC = 65:</strong> You're "The Sage" - wise, patient, helpful</p>
                        <p><strong>Friday VC = 25:</strong> You're "The Asshole" - reactive, defensive, harmful</p>
                        <p><strong>Same person. Different capacity. Different archetype.</strong></p>
                    </div>

                    <p class="fluidity-truth">This is why labels fail. You're not "an addict" or "a narcissist" or "a saint."</p>
                    <p class="fluidity-truth"><strong>You're a consciousness interface with variable capacity.</strong></p>
                    <p class="fluidity-truth">Raise VC → Archetype shifts naturally.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

